resource.name: resource

revisions.description: Added chassis switch (e.g. SBx8100) descriptions to stack-related MIB objects
MIB revision history dates in descriptions updated.
In standalone mode the AT-RESOURCE-MIB was indexed by the default stack member ID of 1. This has been updated to index by the stack member ID of the device.
Add objects for displaying host information.

resource.description: The AT-RESOURCE-MIB contains objects for displaying system hardware resource information.

rscBoardTable.name: rscBoardTable
rscBoardTable.description: A table of information about boards installed in a device.

rscBoardEntry.name: rscBoardEntry
rscBoardEntry.description: A conceptual row of entries of rscBoardTable.

rscStkId.name: rscStkId
rscStkId.description: The ID of the stack member. It is a number assigned to a stackable unit by the operating system when it is stacked. An initial value of 1 is given to a stand alone unit. For a chassis switch, it corresponds to the card ID.

rscResourceId.name: rscResourceId
rscResourceId.description: The resource ID number of the board. It is a number assigned to a hardware resource when the operating system detects its existence.

rscBoardType.name: rscBoardType
rscBoardType.description: This object indicates the type of the board. Its value can be 'Base', 'Expansion', 'Fan module' or 'PSU', etc.

rscBoardName.name: rscBoardName
rscBoardName.description: This object represents the name of the board. Its value can be 'SwitchBlade x908', 'XEM-12S' or 'AT-PWR05-AC', etc.

rscBoardID.name: rscBoardID
rscBoardID.description: This object represents the ID number of the board. Its value is an Allied Telesis assigned number, such as 274 for the XEM-12S, or 255 for the AT-9924Ts.

rscBoardBay.name: rscBoardBay
rscBoardBay.description: This object indicates the board installation location. Its value can be 'Bay1', 'Bay2' or 'PSU1', etc. For a base board, it has a value of a single character space.

rscBoardRevision.name: rscBoardRevision
rscBoardRevision.description: This object represents the revision number of the board.

rscBoardSerialNumber.name: rscBoardSerialNumber
rscBoardSerialNumber.description: This object represents the serial number of the board.

hostInfoDRAM.name: hostInfoDRAM
hostInfoDRAM.description: This object indicates the host DRAM information.

hostInfoFlash.name: hostInfoFlash
hostInfoFlash.description: This object indicates the host Flash information.

hostInfoUptime.name: hostInfoUptime
hostInfoUptime.description: This object represents the host up time.

hostInfoBootloaderVersion.name: hostInfoBootloaderVersion
hostInfoBootloaderVersion.description: This object represents the host boot loader version.
